reviews.text: Differ to other brands, this one allows to adjust the dimming range using a trimmer potentiometer on the PCB. It’s simple but would not recommend doing it unless you have some electrician’s experience. The unit makes very slight buzz in the mid dimming range. It can be fixed by adding some spacers over the inductor. Still, I would not recommend doing it unless you are an electronics pro. Assembly is fairly simple. My conclusion is that the dimmer is pretty decent.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on April 27, 2025
reviews.title: Better than another one I tried.

reviews.text: The wiring diagram shows the location of the on/off/dimmer switch on the WRONG end. I didn't pick up on this until I had completed the first connection. I noticed the word LOAD was on the circuit board. Decided that had to be true. Swapped the wiring around and it works fine. It seems SO FUNDAMENTAL to get the diagram right. Obviously no one at the company is paying attention. The quality of the switch itself seem very good. I would purchase again if I needed.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on July 25, 2024
reviews.title: Diagram Not Completely Correct

reviews.productTitle: Inline Lamp Switch 2-Pack, Full Range Rotary Dimmer Switch, Cord Switch Replacement for Floor Lamp, Table Lamp, Pendant Light, Fit for Incandescent, Halogen Bulbs, Dimmable LED Lights
reviews.text: I was looking for an inline dimmer for a couple of lamps. This was just what I needed. It was a simple process to install, you only need wire cutters, wire strippers and a small Phillips head screwdriver. Directions are simple to follow. I’m a DIY’er so it took me about 10 minutes start to finish to install one. if you are using this with an LED bulb it must be the type that is dimmable (it will say “dimmable” on the box and on the base of the bulb). This is truly a variable dimmer from full Off to full on.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.title: Works great, easy to install
